0. install full raspberry pi os configuration.  
1. enable camera via raspi-config.
2. apt-get update ; apt-get upgrade -y; apt-get dist-upgrade -y
3. sudo apt-get install sense-hat build-essential git
4. # install pycamera library
4a. sudo apt-get install python-setuptools
4b. easy_install --user picamera
5. git clone https://github.com/japharl/kapcode.git
6. sudo chmod -R 777 /home/pi/kapcode/*
7. sudo chown -R pi:pi /home/pi/kapcode/*
8. sudo chmod 777 /etc/rc.local
8a. sudo apt-get install cpanminus
8b. sudo cpanm Proc::Background File::Path File::Slurper
9. sudo vi /etc/rc.local
# Add line:
nohup bash -x /home/pi/kapcode/init.sh &

# Optional

10. sudo apt-get install lighttpd 
11. vi /etc/lighttpd.conf
Change server.root to:
/home/pi/kapcode/photos
Then (while taking photos) point to http://[ip]/ for latest photo.  Hit referesh if needed.
